{"id":241251898,"title":"An Improved Criterion for Clustering Based on the Posterior Similarity Matrix","authors":["Arno Fritsch","Katja Ickstadt"],"_abstract":"ABSTRACT In this paper we address the problem of choosing a single clustering estimate ^c based on an MCMC sample of clusterings c(1);c(2) :::;c(M) from the posterior distribution of a Bayesian cluster model. Methods to derive ^c based on the posterior similarity matrix, a matrix with entries P(ci = cjjy), the posterior probabilities that the observations i and j are in the same cluster, are reviewed and discussed. Minimization of a com- monly used loss function for this purpose by Binder (1978) is shown to be equivalent to maximizing the Rand index between estimated and true clustering. We propose a new criterion for choosing an estimated cluster- ing, the posterior expected adjusted Rand index with the true clustering, which outperforms Binder's loss, MAP and an ad hoc criterion in a sim- ulation study. An application to Fisher's Iris data is also provided. Keywords: Adjusted Rand index; Bayesian inference; Cluster analysis; Markov chain Monte Carlo; Loss functions.","cited_in":[{"id":280831448,"url":"https://www.researchgate.net/publication/280831448_Computational_Statistics_and_Data_Analysis"},{"id":44655656,"url":"https://www.researchgate.net/publication/44655656_Discovering_transcriptional_modules_by_Bayesian_data_integration"},{"id":242486770,"url":"https://www.researchgate.net/publication/242486770_Bayesian_Nonparametric_Regression_for_Diabetes_Deaths"},{"id":44922221,"url":"https://www.researchgate.net/publication/44922221_Bayesian_mixtures_for_cluster_analysis_and_flexible_modeling_of_distributions"},{"id":40272219,"url":"https://www.researchgate.net/publication/40272219_Additive_mixed_models_with_Dirichlet_process_mixture_and_P-spline_priors"},{"id":232225549,"url":"https://www.researchgate.net/publication/232225549_Bayesian_correlated_clustering_to_integrate_multiple_datasets"},{"id":254297949,"u